    "To mathematically justify why deep neural networks (DNNs) can suffer from the extreme event problem, consider the following explanation.",
    "Data imbalance and rare eventsExtreme values are often underrepresented in training data, leading to a model that is not well-equipped to handle them.",
    "When extreme values are underrepresented, the model has fewer examples to learn from, making it difficult to accurately capture its magnitude and pattern.",
